k: CFP Certified Financial Planner via CFP Board requiring education plus examination plus 3-year experience plus ongoing CE 30 hours per 2-year cycle; CFA Chartered Financial Analyst via CFA Institute 3-level examination over typical 4-year completion plus 4-year experience; ChFC Chartered Financial Consultant via The American College; CIMA Certified Investment Management Analyst via Investments & Wealth Institute; PFS Personal Financial Specialist via AICPA for CPAs. Securities licensure via FINRA: Series 7 General Securities Representative plus Series 65 Investment Adviser Representative plus Series 66 combined IAR plus Series 63 state securities plus Series 6 mutual funds limited. Florida HNW + UHNW wealth migration 2020-2026 driving substantial AUM growth for Florida-based advisory practices with Sun Belt corporate relocations plus retiree wealth migration plus international wealth migration from Latin America plus Europe plus Canada plus Miami plus Palm Beach plus Naples plus Boca Raton plus Fort Lauderdale emerging as major U.S. wealth management hubs alongside multi-family office sector expansion. Mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income framework with 24-month averaging plus AUM growth continuity narrative documenting AUM trajectory plus client count plus average account size plus retention rate plus new client acquisition rate plus organic versus market-driven growth. B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp framework for RIA equity K-1 distributions with 2-year personal returns plus 2-year firm entity returns Form 1065 partnership or Form 1120-S S-corp plus K-1 schedules plus partnership shareholder agreement excerpt plus ownership percentage plus Form 1084 cash-flow analysis at firm entity level adding back depreciation plus amortization plus business use of office plus entity non-cash expenses. Wirehouse deferred compensation: vested portions already received count in 2-year income picture plus unvested deferred compensation generally not 